article.headline: Lehigh 78, Lafayette 73
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Kevin Tempest scored 13 points to lead Lehigh to a 78-73 victory over Lafayette on Sunday in a showdown for first place in the Patriot League. Tempest led five Lehigh players in double-digits in a game that saw eight lead changes. It was the 200th meeting between the schools. With the game tied at 70 with 5:57 left, Jason Mgebroff hit two free throws and Austen Rowland scored a 3-pointer to give Lehigh (17-8, 10-2) a 75-71 lead. Mgebroff and Rowland each finished with 12. Justin DeBerry made two foul shots to help Lafayette (18-7, 9-3) close within two, but Dayne Mickelson's layup with 29 seconds remaining iced the game for Lehigh. DeBerry and Winston Davis each scored 15 for Lafayette. Sean Knitter added 14 and Pat Betley chipped in 11. On Jan. 23, Lehigh overcame a 10-point deficit with 3:33 remaining in regulation to force overtime, but Lafayette held on for a 111-104 victory.
